                     <!-- ADMINISTRATIVE INFORMATION -->
            <scopecontent>
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                                 <p>This collection contains photocopies, transcripts, and microfilm copies of three separate sets of records. The first set of records (1819-32) contains letters and inspector reports pertaining to Fort Armstrong, Ill. These documents were copied from the Quartermaster General&#039;s Office and the Inspector General&#039;s Office. The next set of records (1819-43) are reports of the Inspector General&#039;s Office regarding troop inspections, the condition of troops, and instructions and recommendations regarding forts. The final set of records (1822-43) are mostly ordnance letters regarding mining and related business activities in the lead mines at Galena, Ill.</p>
                                 <p>The documents were copied from originals in the National Archives in 1973.</p>
                        </scopecontent>
            


